		<p>Nadine — Great! I hope he&#8217;ll love it! Yes, I do freeze it. This allows the layers to stay put and remain neat when unmolding and dressing it up with frosting. It makes a HUGE difference and it&#8217;s a really common restaurant practice. This cake has no ingredients that suffer in the freezer, so the flavor is not effected, so long as it&#8217;s only in there for a day or two. Like with anything, keeping it in the freezer too long may mean freezer burn.</p>

		<div class="reply">
				</div>
